Victor Moore https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victor_Moore 0 Victor Frederick Moore (February 24, 1876 – July 23, 1962) was an American actor of stage and screen, as well as a comedian, writer, and director, most significantly a major Broadway star from the late 1920s through the 1930s.
